         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_031703451.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e8633"> </a>Removing the rear footpegs
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8636"> </a>Removal of the rear RH footpeg is described in detail; the LH footpeg can be removed following the same procedure.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8639"> </a>Loosen the screws&nbsp;(5) and remove rear RH footpeg (6) from the frame.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_031903452.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8644"> </a>If necessary, remove footpeg rubber block (7).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8646"> </a>Remove the circlip (8) thereby releasing the pin (9).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8648"> </a>Support footpeg (3) and remove pin (9) from footpeg holder plate (6), paying attention not to release ball (11) and spring
            (12).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8650"> </a>Slide out footpeg (3) from its seat and collect spring (12) and ball (11).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8652"> </a>Remove the spring stopper (13).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_032003453.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="titoleto"><a name="d3e8658"> </a>Handle kit
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8660"> </a>The handle kit can be installed to the rear LH footpeg holder plate (18).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8662"> </a>Undo the screw (16), and collect spring (17) to remove handle (15).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8664"> </a>When reassembling, make sure pin (21) is in place on plate (18); if necessary, refit and drive it fully home on hole (A) on
            rear LH footpeg holder plate (10).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8666"> </a>Insert spring (17) ends (B) inside hole (C) on footpeg (18).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8668"> </a>Fit handle (15), by starting screw (16).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8671"> </a>When installing handle (15), fit the other end (B) of spring (17) into hole (D) on handle and match pin (21) with the relevant
            seat on handle.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8673"> </a>Tighten screw (16) to a torque of 20 Nm Â± 10%.
         </div>
      </div>
